            "title": "Applications in high-dimensional statistics"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 108047,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The central element in the successful implementation of a proximal algorithm is the ability to compute the proximity operator of the functions present in the optimization problem.",
